 as name,

 as opened_at,

 as tax_rate
), source as (

    select * from __dbt__cte__raw_stores

),

renamed as (

    select

        ----------  ids
        id as location_id,

        ---------- text
        name as location_name,

        ---------- numerics
        tax_rate,

        ---------- timestamps
        date_trunc('day', opened_at) as opened_date

    from source

)

    cast(1 as character varying(256))
 as order_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as location_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as customer_id, cast(null as INTEGER) as subtotal_cents, cast(null as INTEGER) as tax_paid_cents, cast(null as INTEGER) as order_total_cents, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as subtotal, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as tax_paid, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as order_total, cast(null as DATE) as ordered_at
union all
select 
    
    cast(2 as character varying(256))
 as order_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as location_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as customer_id, cast(null as INTEGER) as subtotal_cents, cast(null as INTEGER) as tax_paid_cents, cast(null as INTEGER) as order_total_cents, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as subtotal, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as tax_paid, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as order_total, cast(null as DATE) as ordered_at
),  __dbt__cte__order_items as (

-- Fixture for order_items
select 
    
    cast(1 as character varying(256))
 as order_item_id, 
    
    cast(1 as character varying(256))
 as order_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as product_id, cast(null as DATE) as ordered_at, cast(null as character varying(256)) as product_name, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as product_price, 
    
    cast(True as BOOLEAN)
 as is_food_item, 
    
    cast(False as BOOLEAN)
 as is_drink_item, cast(null as DECIMAL(38,2)) as supply_cost
union all
select 
    
    cast(2 as character varying(256))
 as order_item_id, 
    
    cast(1 as character varying(256))
 as order_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as product_id, cast(null as DATE) as ordered_at, cast(null as character varying(256)) as product_name, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as product_price, 
    
    cast(False as BOOLEAN)
 as is_food_item, 
    
    cast(True as BOOLEAN)
 as is_drink_item, cast(null as DECIMAL(38,2)) as supply_cost
union all
select 
    
    cast(3 as character varying(256))
 as order_item_id, 
    
    cast(2 as character varying(256))
 as order_id, cast(null as character varying(256)) as product_id, cast(null as DATE) as ordered_at, cast(null as character varying(256)) as product_name, cast(null as DECIMAL(16,2)) as product_price, 
    
    cast(True as BOOLEAN)
 as is_food_item, 
    
    cast(False as BOOLEAN)
 as is_drink_item, cast(null as DECIMAL(38,2)) as supply_cost
), orders as (

    select * from __dbt__cte__stg_orders

),

order_items as (

    select * from __dbt__cte__order_items

),

order_items_summary as (

    select
        order_id,

        sum(supply_cost) as order_cost,
        sum(product_price) as order_items_subtotal,
        count(order_item_id) as count_order_items,
        sum(
            case
                when is_food_item then 1
                else 0
            end
        ) as count_food_items,
        sum(
            case
                when is_drink_item then 1
                else 0
            end
        ) as count_drink_items

    from order_items

    group by 1

),

compute_booleans as (

    select
        orders.*,

        order_items_summary.order_cost,
        order_items_summary.order_items_subtotal,
        order_items_summary.count_food_items,
        order_items_summary.count_drink_items,
        order_items_summary.count_order_items,
        order_items_summary.count_food_items > 0 as is_food_order,
        order_items_summary.count_drink_items > 0 as is_drink_order

    from orders

    left join
        order_items_summary
        on orders.order_id = order_items_summary.order_id

),

customer_order_count as (

    select
        *,

        row_number() over (
            partition by customer_id
            order by ordered_at asc
        ) as customer_order_number

    from compute_booleans

)

select * from customer_order_count
